{
  "text": "Based on analysis of numerous genetic targets (Table 7) , Baylisascaris is most closely related to the genus Ascaris. The entire mitochondrial genome has been sequenced for four speciesd B. transfuga, B. ailuri, B. schroederi and B. procyonis (all samples from China) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Phylogenetic analyses of these mitochondrial genomes and concatenated partial mitochondrial and nuclear genes (12S rDNA, 18S rDNA and 28S rDNA) provide the strongest support for the relatedness of the genus Baylisascaris with Ascaris and other members of the order Ascaridida [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
